data.content:
**Yes, C# fully supports `stackalloc`'d `Span<nint>` and `Span<nuint>`.** Both work without requiring `unsafe` context — you just assign directly to a `Span<nint>` or `Span<nuint>`:

```csharp
Span<nint>  signed   = stackalloc nint[4];
Span<nuint> unsigned = stackalloc nuint[3];
```

On this 64-bit system, `nint`/`nuint` are 8 bytes each, so `nint.MaxValue` is `9223372036854775807` and `nuint.MaxValue` is `18446744073709551615` — the same as `long.MaxValue` and `ulong.MaxValue` respectively.
